	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="">RE: Druids don't need ac</a> <a id="fs8" href="#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 25th 10:34 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=35794"><span id=" ">Miladian</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">21 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>If a druid is getting hit during a fight, the druid is doing something wrong, or your tanks aren't taunting enough. In the upper levels, meaning by the time you could actually get this piece which would be 55+, druids aren't getting healing aggro, as they are rarely the main healers in the group. They aren't meleeing hardly at all, and shouldn't have been meleeing past level 30 anyways, so they can't be aggroing that way either. <br/><br/>About the only way a druid would be getting any aggro would be if he over nuked or is snaring, and if you make it to 55+ you know enough not to do that by then.<br/><br/>Besides, all the AC in the world isn't going to save a druid in a fight if he has the aggro on him. You don't have the HP's or the defense skills of a hybrid or a tank to survive very long. But all that being said, this would be a very nice druid item, but not something reserved for a druid, as they will more than likely have 200+ WIS by 55+.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
